description: A fast-growing tropical tree that produces delicious, juicy mangoes during summer. Its dense green canopy offers shade, while its sweet fruits are rich in vitamins and minerals.
A hardy fruit tree that grows in various climates, yielding guavas packed with Vitamin C. Its low maintenance nature makes it a favorite for home gardens.
A large tropical tree that bears the world’s biggest fruit, the jackfruit. Its sweet and aromatic flesh is both nutritious and filling, and the tree itself provides generous shade.
Known as the ‘Flame of the Forest’, this tree bursts into a vibrant display of red flowers every summer. Perfect for beautifying avenues and gardens.
A fragrant flowering tree that adorns gardens with its delicate white blossoms. Widely cherished in traditional rituals and perfumery.
A striking ornamental tree famous for its brilliant orange-red blossoms. Its wide canopy adds a festive charm to parks and roadsides.
A majestic shade tree with a vast canopy and iconic aerial roots. Revered in many cultures, it offers shelter to countless birds and animals.
A medicinal shade tree with powerful insect-repelling properties. Its leaves, bark, and seeds are widely used in traditional remedies.
A fast-growing tree with umbrella-like canopy and soft pink flowers. Perfect for roadside planting to provide cool shade.
A small to medium tree producing fruits rich in Vitamin C and antioxidants. Its fruits are used in Ayurvedic tonics for boosting immunity.
